#Cleaning the text column
import string
import nltk
import numpy as np 
from nltk.stem.porter import *
from datetime import datetime as dt


#removing pattern from tweets

def remove_pattern(input_txt, pattern):
                                r = re.findall(pattern, input_txt)
                                for i in r:
                                input_txt = re.sub(i, ' ', input_txt)
                                return input_txt   

# removing twitter handles (@user)
df_sample['Clean_Text'] = np.vectorize(remove_pattern)(df_sample['Text'], "@[\w]*#")
#removing urls    
df_sample['Clean_Text'] = np.vectorize(remove_pattern)(df_sample['Text'], "https?://[A-Za-z./]'*")

#removing special characters, numbers, punctuations
df_sample['Clean_Text'] = df_sample['Clean_Text'].str.replace("[^a-zA-Z]", " ")
#removing words of length lesser than 2      
df_sample['Clean_Text'] = df_sample['Clean_Text'].apply(lambda x: ' '.join([w for w in x.split() if len(w)>2]))

#removing meaningless words in the text column
words = set(nltk.corpus.words.words())

def clean_sent(sent):
                                return " ".join(w for w in nltk.wordpunct_tokenize(sent)
                                if w.lower() in words or not w.isalpha())

df_sample['Clean_Text'] = df_sample['Clean_Text'].apply(clean_sent)
